5.62. 
Transfer of succession to the State
1. The heritable property shall pass by right of succession to the State if:
(1) the property is bequeathed to the State by will;
2) the deceased has no heirs either by operation of law or by will;
3. no heir has accepted the inheritance;
4) all the heirs have been deprived of the right of succession.
2. If there are no heirs at law and only part of the deceased's estate has been bequeathed by will, the remainder shall pass to the State.
3. The State shall be liable for the debts of the deceased to the extent of the fair value of the property inherited.
